SIMPLE: enterprise
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enterprise
<hw>En"ter*prise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>enterprise</ets>, fr. <ets>entreprendre</ets> to undertake;
<ets>entre</ets> between (L. <ets>inter</ets>) + <ets>prendre</ets> to
take. See <er>Inter</er>, and <er>Emprise</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>That which is undertaken; something attempted to be performed; a
work projected which involves activity, courage, energy, and the like; a
bold, arduous, or hazardous attempt; an undertaking; <as>as, a manly
<ex>enterprise</ex>; a warlike <ex>enterprise</ex>.</as></def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their hands can not perform their <qex>enterprise</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Job v. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Willingness or eagerness to engage in labor which
requires boldness, promptness, energy, and like qualities; <as>as, a man
of great <ex>enterprise</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enterprise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enterprise
<hw>En"ter*prise</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To undertake;
to begin and attempt to perform; to venture upon.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The business must be <qex>enterprised</qex> this night.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What would I not renounce or <qex>enterprise</qex> for you!</q>
<rj><qau>T. Otway.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To treat with hospitality; to entertain.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Him at the threshold met, and well did <qex>enterprise</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enterprise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Enterprise
<hw>En"ter*prise</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To undertake an enterprise,
or something hazardous or difficult.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enterpriser</ent>⟦br⟧
